<org.eclipse.epf.uma:ProcessDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-M3YoGLVicj1Ae9SNe1OZcQ" name="cost_inception_recommend_candidate_solutions,_1iySMfr_EdmQwKBXhQotBQ" guid="-M3YoGLVicj1Ae9SNe1OZcQ" version="7.1.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;Top&quot; name=&quot;Top&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The goal is to recommend one or several candidate solutions to be further investigated in the next iterations or to&#xD;
    recommend a single solution to be implemented in the construction phase (final recommendation).&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    At the end of each iteration of the elaboration phase, the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.cots/tasks/cots_recommend_solution_6C4FE964.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{74E63EE3-FA99-4409-A00D-CD863B1D6868}&quot;>Recommend Solution&lt;/a> task (introduced in the inception phase) is&#xD;
    performed to either recommend one or several candidate solutions to be further investigated in the next iterations or&#xD;
    to recommend a single solution to be implemented in the construction phase (final recommendation).&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    A final recommendation is made once all the stakeholders agree that one solution, among the candidate solutions, is the&#xD;
    one feasible solution that best meets the business goals, demands of the use cases and non-functional requirements,&#xD;
    architectural and design constraints, and project management constraints such as time, money, people, and scope with&#xD;
    reasonable risks, once this solution demonstrates sufficient stability in requirements and architecture and addresses&#xD;
    all architecturally significant risks.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The final recommendation is a proposal to acquire the COTS packages needed to form the selected solution and to&#xD;
    implement this solution in the construction phase. It includes the rationale for choosing one solution and rejecting&#xD;
    the other candidates. Recommendations are captured in the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.cots/workproducts/cots_solution_recommendation_E9834644.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{A4C2C8B3-4905-4C89-86E4-D3FBDAE512BF}&quot;>Solution Recommendation&lt;/a>. Note that in order to make a recommendation,&#xD;
    you may need to update the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.cots/workproducts/cots_cumulative_solution_eval_summary_F949E9A6.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{E29F5020-BF6D-4D40-8BC9-52D25F9DD183}&quot;>Cumulative Candidate Solution Evaluation Summary&lt;/a> which provides an&#xD;
    easy comparison of candidate solutions.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Consequently, recommending solution(s) is done by performing the following RUP task (note that other RUP tasks and&#xD;
    artifacts may be applicable, but this is the minimum recommended set):&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
